"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/686248","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-02-20","<p>The Personalisation Pathfinder commenced in April 2015 and finished at the end of September 2016. It was running in three Jobcentre Plus Districts which were Greater Wessex, South West Wales and Surrey and Sussex.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The evaluation of the Personalisation Pathfinder continues. As is standard practice the findings will be published in due course.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="5"><p>The allocated budget for the Personalisation Pathfinder</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Financial year</p></td><td><p>14/15</p></td><td><p>15/16</p></td><td><p>16/17</p></td><td><p>17/18</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Allocated Budget</p></td><td><p><strong>£115,000</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£5,435,000</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£955,000</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£100,000</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","63524 ; 63525","2017-02-20T17:22:15.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/686248/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/686248/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/686248/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-02-07","Employment Schemes: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment his Department has made of the effectiveness of the personalisation pathfinder initiative; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","63523"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/686249","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-02-14","<p>The information requested is not available. Neither the Ministry of Justice, who publish the official appeal statistics, nor the Department for Work and Pensions, which collates its own data on appeals, has information about appeals made only against <em>refusals.</em> The information that is available is in relation to <em>all</em> appeals lodged for any given benefit.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","63474 ; 63475 ; 63476 ; 63489","2017-02-14T15:05:24.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/686249/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/686249/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/686249/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-02-07","Incapacity Benefit: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many appeals were lodged against decisions to refuse incapacity benefit in (a) Blackburn and Darwen, (b) Burnley, (c) Hyndburn, (d) Pendle, (e) Ribble Valley and (f) Rossendale and Chorley in (i) 2011, (ii) 2012, (iii) 2013, (iv) 2014, (v) 2015 and (vi) 2016.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","63477"
