"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685432","HM Treasury","false","2017-02-13","<p>The Government supports the G20’s initiative to reform inefficient fossil fuel subsidies and has offered to be a peer reviewer. However we do not believe the UK is a suitable candidate for peer review under this process as we have no fossil fuel subsidies according to the definition adopted by the UK and other EU members of the G20.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","63284","2017-02-13T13:59:34.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685432/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685432/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685432/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-02-06","Fossil Fuels: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the Declaration on global economic and political challenges made by the G7 leaders at the Ise-Shima Summit in May 2016, what progress the Government has made on its commitment to ending inefficient fossil fuel subsidies by 2025.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","63285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685433","HM Treasury","false","2017-02-13","<p>The Government supports the G20’s initiative to reform inefficient fossil fuel subsidies and has offered to be a peer reviewer. However we do not believe the UK is a suitable candidate for peer review under this process as we have no fossil fuel subsidies according to the definition adopted by the UK and other EU members of the G20.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","63285","2017-02-13T13:59:34.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685433/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685433/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685433/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-02-06","Fossil Fuels: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the G20 Leaders' Communique made at the Hangzhou Summit in September 2016, whether the Government will participate in the fossil fuel subsidy peer review process.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","63284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685434","HM Treasury","false","2017-02-14","<p>HM Treasury is located in the Government Offices Great George Street (GOGGS) building with five other Government departments. While each department has its own pass, all the passes give access to all departmental areas within the building. The number of security passes issued is subject to frequent change due to staff turnover. The numbers mentioned below are correct for 13 February 2017.</p><p> </p><p>(a) The number of security passes for the GOGGS building that are issued to people not directly employed by HM Treasury is 5971;</p><p> </p><p>(b) The number of security passes for the GOGGS building that are issued to people who are not civil servants who work in the GOGGS complex is 343.</p><p> </p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2017-02-14T09:49:54.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685434/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685434/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685434/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-02-06","Treasury: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many security passes into his Department are issued to people (a) not directly employed by and (b) who are not civil servants who work in his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","63277"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685435","Church Commissioners","false","2017-02-08","<p>Most of the people who work at Church House, Westminster are not employed solely by the Church Commissioners. Staff of the National Church Institutions (NCIs) which include the Church Commissioners are mostly employed jointly by the Institutions.</p><p>In that context I refer the Hon Gentleman to my previous answer to question 62530 answered on 06 February 2017 which stated that only NCI employees enjoy full access to our premises and that other groups have limited and time-limited access. These groups include diocesan bishops, members of General Synod, contractors and tenants.</p><p>A) To date the percentage of passes issued to NCIs staff is 56.24%</p><p>B) None of the staff of the NCIs are civil servants.</p>","Meriden","Dame Caroline Spelman",,"2017-02-08T17:59:10.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685435/answer","Biography information for Dame Caroline Spelman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685435/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685435/answer",,,,,,,,"9","Church Commissioners","Church Commissioners","2017-02-06","Church Commissioners: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the right hon. Member for Meriden, representing the Church Commissioners, how many security passes into the Church Commissioners are issued to people (a) not directly employed by and (b) who are not civil servants who work in the Church Commissioners.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","63257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685436","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-14","<p>The information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-02-14T17:04:48.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685436/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685436/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685436/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-06","Department for Communities and Local Government: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many security passes into his Department are issued to people (a) not directly employed by and (b) who are not civil servants who work in his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","63258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685437","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-09","<p>It is open to any councils to submit proposals for local government reorganisation which I will consider carefully as soon as practicable after their submission. I understand certain councils in Dorset intend shortly to submit such proposals which I shall consider accordingly.</p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-02-09T16:58:05.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685437/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685437/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685437/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-06","Local Government: Dorset","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what his Department's policy is on the length of time that district councils in Dorset be allowed to (a) consider and (b) present alternative proposals on the future of local government structures in that area.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","63309"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685438","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-09","<p>It is a matter for councils locally to decide on their partnership arrangements.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-02-09T16:58:36.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685438/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685438/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685438/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-06","Local Government: Conditions of Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what his Department's policy is on the termination of district council partnership working arrangements where the future structure of local government is under consideration; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","63310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685439","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-09","<p>The Cities and Local Government Devolution Act 2016 provides that the secondary legislation about reorganisation may be made, if Parliament approves, providing one council in the area consents. We have made clear that if a reorganisation proposal is to be implemented there needs to be a good deal of local support.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-02-09T16:59:13.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685439/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685439/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685439/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-06","Unitary Councils","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether it is his Department's policy to accept proposals for unitarisation in the event that there is a disagreement between the councils affected by those proposals.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","63311"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685440","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-09","<p>We have issued no such guidance; how councils prepare proposals for reorganisation and the arrangements they have for collaboration and joint working is a matter for them.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-02-09T17:00:04.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685440/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685440/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-06","Unitary Councils","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what guidance his Department has issued to local authorities on requirements for consulting with all councils that have (a) accepted and (b) rejected proposals on unitarisation; and what steps his Department has taken to encourage reconciliation in such cases.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","63312"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685441","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-09","<p>The Government recognises issues of affordability in the Private Rented Sector. The Housing White Paper launched on 7th February sets out how the Government will fix the broken housing market by boosting housing supply, thereby helping to improve affordability in the long term.</p><p>The Government also recognises the important role that buy-to-let landlords play in the UK housing market and economy.</p><p>At Summer Budget 2015, the Government set out a package of measures to reduce the budget deficit, rebalance the economy and make the tax system fairer.</p><p>HMRC’s analysis shows that only 1 in 5 landlords will be affected by the tax changes on property finance costs (such as mortgage interest or interest on loans to buy furnishings).</p><p>The Government does not expect this to have a large impact on house prices or rent levels due to the small overall proportion of the housing market affected. The Office of Budget Responsibility also expects any impact to be small.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-02-09T17:07:08.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685441/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685441/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685441/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-06","Housing: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will make an assessment of recent trends in buy-to-let cost rises; and what steps his Department is taking to mitigate against any adverse effect from significant changes in property prices.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","63153"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685442","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-09","<p>My Department does not publish projections for house building.</p><p>Because of the decisions this Government has taken, the British economy is fundamentally strong and will continue to be strong as we negotiate our departure from the EU. The Bank of England expects the UK economy to grow this year 2 per cent, up on their previous prediction in November of 1.4 per cent.</p><p>The Housing White Paper recognises that there are challenges and opportunities ahead. In some parts of the country the house building industry draws heavily on migrant labour. So this is the moment for the industry to raise its game and invest in growing its own workforce, and in new and innovative methods of construction. We will continue to monitor any developments within the house building industry.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-02-09T17:03:54.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685442/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685442/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685442/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-06","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will make an assessment of the potential effect of the UK leaving the EU on house-building projections.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","63154"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685443","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-16","<p>The statistics published at this link contain the information that you have requested:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/local-authority-housing-statistics-data-returns-for-2015-to-2016</p><p /> <p> </p><p> </p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-02-16T13:35:05.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685443/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685443/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685443/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-06","Rents: Arrears","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what recent assessment he has made of the (a) level and (b) extent of arrears of tenants in the (i) social and (ii) private rented sector.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","63188"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685444","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-27","<p>The rateable value threshold for a small property in the 2017 transitional relief scheme was increased from £25,500 to £28,000 in Greater London and from £18,000 to £20,000 elsewhere, compared to the 2010 scheme. This increase was in line with the overall effect of the business rates revaluation on rateable values, and helps to maintain the support the scheme provides to small businesses.</p><p>The Government announced this as part of the consultation on the 2017 transitional relief scheme. The Department regularly has discussions with representative bodies for the small business sector on a range of issues, including changes to the business rates system.</p><p>At Budget 2016, the Government announced that the threshold for Small Business Rate Relief Scheme would double from April 2017, from £6000 to £12,000. As a result of this change over 600,000 small businesses will pay no rates at all.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","63191","2017-02-27T18:05:03.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685444/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685444/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685444/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-06","Small Businesses: Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what discussions his Department has had with small businesses ahead of the introduction of proposed changes to business rate rateable values on the definition of a small business.","false","Biography information for Craig Tracey","North Warwickshire","Craig Tracey","63190"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685445","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-27","<p>The rateable value threshold for a small property in the 2017 transitional relief scheme was increased from £25,500 to £28,000 in Greater London and from £18,000 to £20,000 elsewhere, compared to the 2010 scheme. This increase was in line with the overall effect of the business rates revaluation on rateable values, and helps to maintain the support the scheme provides to small businesses.</p><p>The Government announced this as part of the consultation on the 2017 transitional relief scheme. The Department regularly has discussions with representative bodies for the small business sector on a range of issues, including changes to the business rates system.</p><p>At Budget 2016, the Government announced that the threshold for Small Business Rate Relief Scheme would double from April 2017, from £6000 to £12,000. As a result of this change over 600,000 small businesses will pay no rates at all.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","63190","2017-02-27T18:05:03.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685445/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685445/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685445/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-06","Small Businesses: Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if his Department will increase transitional thresholds for business rate relief.","false","Biography information for Craig Tracey","North Warwickshire","Craig Tracey","63191"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685446","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-09","<p>The Government supports steps to increase the number of Changing Places toilets. Research into the effectiveness of the statutory guidance which supports Building Regulations’ requirements for access for non domestic buildings is currently being finalised. The research has covered provision of Changing Places toilets. The research will be published in due course and the Government will consider carefully any findings relating to Changing Places toilets.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-02-09T17:05:26.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685446/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685446/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685446/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-06","Public Lavatories: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether his Department has made an assessment of the potential merits of Changing Places toilet facilities in public places; and if he will include requirements for such facilities in any future disability strategy.","false","Biography information for Richard Arkless","Dumfries and Galloway","Richard  Arkless","63204"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685447","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-14","<p>The Creative Industries are one of the UK’s greatest success stories, contributing over £87 billion to the economy (5.7% GVA) and over £19 billion in exports.</p><p> </p><p>We are working closely for example through the Creative Industries Council (CIC), who represent the whole of the creative industries, to understand both the possible opportunities and impacts presented by the UK’s decision leaving the EU.</p><p> </p><p>We have also hosted a series of roundtables with businesses and industry representatives from across the creative industries to discuss these matters. We are committed to helping our world-leading creative industries thrive in a post-brexit Britain. We have also announced a sector review of the creative industries as part of the recently published Industrial Strategy Green Paper to help underpin their future prosperity.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-02-14T14:22:25.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685447/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685447/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685447/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-06","Arts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps she is taking to ensure that the diverse needs of the creative industries will be supported after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Nigel Adams","Selby and Ainsty","Nigel Adams","63239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685448","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-14","<p>The Government agrees that copyright owners should remain able to tailor content to different markets and to license on a territorial basis. While we remain in the EU we will continue to take an active part in negotiations regarding the digital single market ensuring British views are heard.</p><p> </p><p>After the UK leaves the EU it will continue to be a member of the Berne Convention and other copyright treaties which recognise the territoriality of copyright.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-02-14T14:24:13.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685448/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685448/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685448/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-06","Copyright","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what her policy is on whether the UK will be able to protect the territoriality of copyright after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Nigel Adams","Selby and Ainsty","Nigel Adams","63240"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685449","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-13","<p>I meet representatives from the Premier League on a regular basis to discuss a wide range of issues including progress on the pledge made by Premier League clubs to make their grounds more accessible to disabled spectators.</p><p> </p><p>I have recently received the Premier League’s interim report on the progress made by Premier League clubs to meet their pledge on a number commitments to make the clubs’ stadia with accessibility standards by August 2017.</p><p> </p><p>Ensuring sport is inclusive and accessible for spectators remains a priority, and I want to continue to see concerted action taken by clubs to fulfil their legal obligations towards disabled supporters. The Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC) is the regulatory body responsible for enforcing the Equality Act 2010. The EHRC has powers to ensure service providers, including sports stadia, fulfil their legal obligations under the Act.</p><p> </p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-02-13T12:32:15.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685449/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685449/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685449/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-06","Football: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions her Department has had with the Premier League to ensure that football clubs not meeting disability access criteria make the necessary improvements.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","63109"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685450","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-13","<p>The English Football League (EFL) have set out a clear accessibility work plan which seeks to ensure a better matchday experience for disabled spectators. The EFL have committed to a programme of continual improvement in facilities, in conjunction with their clubs and Level Playing Field. The plan touches on all aspects of the matchday experience and is being implemented over the current season.</p><p> </p><p>Ensuring sport is inclusive and accessible for spectators remains a priority, and I want to continue to see concerted action taken by clubs to fulfil their legal obligations towards disabled supporters. The Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC) is the regulatory body responsible for enforcing the Equality Act 2010 The EHRC has powers to ensure service providers, including sports stadia, fulfil their legal obligations under the Act.</p><p> </p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-02-13T12:31:00.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685450/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685450/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685450/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-06","Football: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps she is taking to help improve disability access at Football League grounds.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","63108"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685451","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-09","<p>The Burghers of Calais sculpture is owned by the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport. Its day-to-day maintenance is the responsibility of The Royal Parks, currently an Agency of the Department for Culture, Media and Sport.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-02-09T08:57:20.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685451/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685451/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685451/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-06","Sculpture: Victoria Tower Gardens","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, who owns the Burghers of Calais sculpture in Victoria Tower Gardens.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","63158"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685452","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-09","<p>I refer the Hon Member to my response to PQ 52415.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-02-09T10:16:47.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685452/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685452/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685452/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-06","Tech North and techUK","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the level of Government funding for (a) Tech UK and (b) Tech North has been in each year from their establishment to date.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","63168"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685453","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-13","<p>Our Sports Strategy sends a clear message to all sports that sports stadia should provide an inclusive environment that welcomes all spectators. While the spotlight on accessibility is rightly on football, we want all sports to ensure they fulfil their legal obligations towards disabled fans. We will be looking to other sports to follow football’s example, to ensure disabled spectators receive the legal requirements that they are entitled to.</p><p> </p><p>Ensuring sport is inclusive and accessible for spectators remains a priority, and I want to continue to see concerted action taken by clubs to fulfil their legal obligations towards disabled supporters. The Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC) is the regulatory body responsible for enforcing the Equality Act 2010 The EHRC has powers to ensure service providers, including sports stadia, fulfil their legal obligations under the Act.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-02-13T12:27:45.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685453/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685453/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685453/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-06","Sportsgrounds: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what recent discussions her Department has had with sports governing bodies on improving disability access at sports stadia.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","63107"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685454","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-14","<p>I refer the hon member to my answer to PQ 62532.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-02-14T14:20:48.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685454/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685454/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685454/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-06","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many security passes into her Department are issued to people (a) not directly employed by and (b) who are not civil servants who work in her Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","63259"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685455","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-09","<p>We have been in regular dialogue with the BBFC since July 2015.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-02-09T13:00:46.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685455/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685455/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685455/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-06","British Board of Film Classification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, on what dates Ministers of her Department have met the British Board of Film Classification to discuss the Digital Economy Bill since July 2015.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","63301"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685456","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-13","<p><br>We have had widespread and ongoing discussions with the digital industry on Data Protection.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-02-13T16:17:11.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685456/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685456/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685456/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-06","Digital Technology: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions she has had with representatives from the digital industries on data protection regulations since the UK's decision to leave the EU.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","63265"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685457","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-14","<p>Ofcom is responsible for promoting Media Literacy, including through annual research on the media lives and attitudes of adults and children, and works closely with other agencies who use the findings to develop specific actions and initiatives to promote Media Literacy. We regularly engage with Ofcom in the discharging of their duties.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","63297 ; 63298","2017-02-14T14:33:26.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685457/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685457/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685457/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-06","Mass Media: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much her Department has spent on promoting media literacy in each year since 2008.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","63296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685458","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-14","<p>Ofcom is responsible for promoting Media Literacy, including through annual research on the media lives and attitudes of adults and children, and works closely with other agencies who use the findings to develop specific actions and initiatives to promote Media Literacy. We regularly engage with Ofcom in the discharging of their duties.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","63296 ; 63298","2017-02-14T14:33:26.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685458/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685458/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685458/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-06","Mass Media: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many officials in her Department work on promoting media literacy.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","63297"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685459","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-14","<p>Ofcom is responsible for promoting Media Literacy, including through annual research on the media lives and attitudes of adults and children, and works closely with other agencies who use the findings to develop specific actions and initiatives to promote Media Literacy. We regularly engage with Ofcom in the discharging of their duties.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","63296 ; 63297","2017-02-14T14:33:26.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685459/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685459/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685459/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-06","Mass Media: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps her Department is taking to promote media literacy.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","63298"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685460","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-10","<p>The Department for Culture Media and Sport leads on data protection policy, which includes implementation of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). There are around 21 officials in the Department contributing to implementation of the GDPR, with many departments across Government also supporting the work.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-02-10T15:34:31.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685460/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685460/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685460/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-06","Data Protection: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many officials in her Department are working on preparations to implement the General Data Protection Regulation.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","63299"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685461","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-10","<p>The information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-10T14:15:01.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685461/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685461/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685461/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-06","Ministry of Defence: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many security passes into his Department are issued to people (a) not directly employed by and (b) who are not civil servants who work in his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","63260"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685462","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-13","<p>The current draft of Joint Doctrine Publication 0-30.2 Unmanned Aircraft Systems discusses the legal framework for the employment of remotely piloted air systems both within and outside areas of &quot;armed conflict&quot;.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-02-13T16:10:47.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685462/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685462/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685462/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-06","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 3 February 2017 to Question 62363, whether the current draft of Joint Doctrine Publication 0-30.2, Unmanned Aircraft Systems, discusses the legal framework for the employment of Unmanned Aircraft Systems (a) within and (b) outside areas of armed conflict.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","63288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685463","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-10","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) is aware of some reports of the mistreatment of civilians by Kurdish forces engaged in the liberation of Mosul. Both Prime Minister Abadi and Kurdish Regional President Barzani have been clear that International Humanitarian Law must be respected and that any allegations of violations will be investigated and those responsible held to account.</p><p>The MOD takes its role in upholding and promoting human rights very seriously. UK troops carrying out building partner capacity training in the Kurdish region of Iraq include International Humanitarian Law as an integral part of that training and the UK continues to lobby the Government of Iraq, Kurdish Regional Government and other authorities to respect International Humanitarian Law.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-02-10T14:13:20.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685463/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685463/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685463/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-06","Iraq: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what reports his Department has received on the mistreatment of Sunni Arab refugees by Kurdish forces following the offensive of Mosul.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","63232"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685464","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-10","<p>The information requested is published regularly by NATO. The most recent figures (from July 2016) are in Table 3 of NATO's Press Release Communique</p><p>PR/CP(2016)116 of 4 July 2016, which can be found at http://www.nato.int/nato_static_fl2014/assets/pdf/pdf_2016_07/20160704_160704-pr2016-116.pdf</p><p>The UK is committed to spend 2% of GDP on defence every year of this decade in accordance with the NATO guidelines.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-02-10T14:14:29.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685464/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685464/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685464/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-06","Defence: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent estimate he has made of the proportion of gross domestic product spent on defence by each other NATO member state.","false","Biography information for Bill Wiggin","North Herefordshire","Bill Wiggin","63233"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685465","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-10","<p>Operations to free Mosul from Daesh rule are being led by the Iraqi security forces, with support from the Global Counter Daesh Coalition to which the UK is a key contributor. Following the announcement by Prime Minister Abadi of the successful liberation of Eastern Mosul, Iraqi forces are now preparing for operations to free the remainder of the city which are likely to start shortly.</p><p>This will continue to be a challenging fight which will take time and patience and, while it would not be appropriate to predict a precise end date, I am confident that Iraqi forces will succeed in the next stage of these operations, as they have to date.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-02-10T14:12:45.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685465/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685465/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685465/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-06","Iraq: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what forecast his Department has made of the likely timescale for the full liberation of Mosul.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","63229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685466","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-09","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 21 November 2016 to Question 53401 from the hon. Member for Llanelli (Nia Griffith).</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-09T15:36:30.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685466/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685466/answer","Hansard Extract 21 November 2016 HOC 53401.docx","Hansard Extract 21 November 2016 HOC 53401.docx","Military Bases:Closures","Military Bases:Closures","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685466/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-06","Military Bases: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he has made an assessment of the socio-economic effect of the proposed MoD site closures announced in 2016; and if he will make a statement.","true","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","63307"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685467","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-09","<p>&quot;A Better Defence Estate&quot; is a military-led review. All military and civilian personnel at sites identified for closure were informed at the time of the announcement through their chain of command. Staff will continue to be kept up to date, through the chain of command, on plans and developments for their sites.</p><p> </p><p>Military personnel currently based at sites identified for closure will be relocated with their unit or re-assigned in accordance with existing career management procedures. As much notice as possible will be provided.</p><p> </p><p>Civilian staff will be expected to honour the mobility obligations if their post is being relocated. Where an individual's post is being relocated outside the scope of their personal mobility obligation they will be managed in accordance with normal Departmental policy and processes.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-09T15:35:48.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685467/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685467/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685467/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-06","Military Bases: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with military and civilian personnel on the proposed MoD site closures; and what assistance his Department plans to give to people required to relocate.","true","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","63308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685468","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-09","<p>When framing the legislation, the Ministry of Defence carefully considered whether it would be practicable to include such agreements. The Single Source Regulations Office will make recommendations to the Secretary of State for Defence in 2017 on changes to the legislation after they have consulted fully on this and other issues.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-02-09T15:35:21.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685468/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685468/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685468/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-06","Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of adopting the recommendation by the Single Source Regulations Office that programmes and platforms procured through foreign military sales should be brought into the single source procurement regulations regime; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","63163"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685469","Ministry of Defence","true","2017-02-09","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 1 November 2016 to Question 49995. The <del class="ministerial">Mechanical</del><ins class="ministerial">Mechanised</ins> Infantry Vehicle project is in the concept phase and it remains too early to provide a timeline by which a decision on numbers can be provided.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-02-09T15:34:58.633Z","2017-02-16T12:30:20.89Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685469/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685469/answer","Hansard Extract 1 November 2016.docx","Hansard Extract 1 November 2016.docx","Armoured Fighting Vehicles","Armoured Fighting Vehicles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685469/answer","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685469/answer/previousversion/35016","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685469/answer/previousversion/35016","Hansard Extract 1 November 2016.docx","Armoured Fighting Vehicles","11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-06","Armoured Fighting Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he plans to announce the final number of vehicles his Department plans to procure as part of the Mechanised Infantry Vehicle programme.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","63162"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685470","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-10","<p>A &quot;Better Defence Estate&quot; is a military led review.</p><p>In announcing the strategy, I confirmed our proposal to consolidate the estate in Wales and create a specialist light infantry centre at St Athan. Our intent remains to relocate the RAF No. 4 School of Technical Training away from St Athan to co-locate with other military training facilities. As the Department had no long term requirement for the Super Hangar, the facility has been sold to enable Aston Martin Limited to develop a car production facility on the site. This is consistent with the decision in 2003 which transferred the majority of the St Athan site to the Welsh Government under a 125 year development lease.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-10T14:13:51.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685470/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685470/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685470/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-06","RAF St Athan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his plans are for the future of his Department's Saint Athan estate; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Christina Rees","Neath","Christina Rees","63112"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685471","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-14","<p>Around 80 UK Service personnel are either embedded with or seconded to the national Armed Forces of the 10 countries involved in Operation RESTORING HOPE. No UK Service personnel are taking part in coalition operations in Yemen.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon",,"2017-02-14T15:53:06.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685471/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685471/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685471/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-06","Yemen: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many UK service personnel are embedded with or seconded to the national armed forces of other countries in the coalition participating in Operation Restoring Hope in Yemen.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","63105"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685472","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-14","<p>The UK does not have any embedded or seconded Service personnel taking part in coalition operations in Yemen.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon",,"2017-02-14T15:51:13.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685472/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685472/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685472/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-06","Yemen: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many UK service personnel have been embedded with or seconded to coalition forces participating in Operation Restoring Hope in Yemen; and what roles those personnel are performing.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","63104"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685473","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-09","<p>The Ministry of Defence places a high priority on assuring the effectiveness of the United Kingdom's independent nuclear deterrent and managing the associated risk.</p><p>We dedicate considerable resource to assessing the threats from emerging capabilities and will apply any necessary mitigation throughout the lifetime of the nuclear deterrent to combat these threats.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-02-09T15:34:22.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685473/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685473/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685473/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-06","Unmanned Marine Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the threat that underwater drones and distributed netted sensors pose, as part of the risk reduction and demonstration phase for the Dreadnought Class submarines.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","63146"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685474","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-09","<p>16th Regiment Royal Artillery is the United Kingdom's short range air defence and air surveillance Regiment. The Regimental establishment is 31 officers and 354 other ranks.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-02-09T15:30:32.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685474/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685474/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685474/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-06","Royal Artillery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the role and establishment is of the 16th Regiment Royal Artillery based at Thorney Island.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","63156"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685475","Department for Education","false","2017-02-09","<p>The data requested on the number of places approved, number of places available and number of children accommodated is published in the ‘Children accommodated in secure children's homes’ Statistical First Release for England and Wales:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/children-accommodated-in-secure-childrens-homes-31-march-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/children-accommodated-in-secure-childrens-homes-31-march-2016</a></p><p>The publication is based on an aggregate return and does not collect information on where children were previously resident.</p><p>The department does not publish nor collect data for Scotland. However, data on available places in secure residential accommodation for Scotland is publicly available at <a href="http://www.sanscotland.org/" target="_blank">http://www.sanscotland.org/</a></p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2017-02-09T15:54:50.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685475/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685475/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685475/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-06","Secure Accommodation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what information her Department holds on how many places there are available in secure residential accommodation for children in (a) England, (b) Scotland and (c) Wales; how many of those places are currently filled; and how many children placed in such accommodation in (i) England were previously resident in (A) Scotland and (B) Wales, (ii) Scotland were previously resident in (A) England and (B) Wales and (iii) Wales were previously resident in (A) England and (B) Scotland.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","63206"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685476","Department for Education","false","2017-02-09","<p>Local authorities hold such information in plans for looked after children and adopted children. This data is not sent to the Department. Local authorities must take account of a family’s needs when planning care for a child in so far as is consistent with the welfare of a child (which remains paramount), as set out in guidance on care placements, available at: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/children-act-1989-care-planning-placement-and-case-review. Where it is not possible, or appropriate, to place siblings together, siblings must be supported to understand the reasons why. Contact arrangements between siblings must be robust and remain under independent review.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","63207 ; 63302","2017-02-09T13:16:55.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685476/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685476/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685476/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-06","Adoption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many adopted children (a) were placed with their full or half siblings in the last three years and (b) who were not so placed have not had contact with their full or half siblings detailed in their adoption order in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","63208"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685477","Department for Education","false","2017-02-09","<p>Local authorities hold such information in plans for looked after children and adopted children. This data is not sent to the Department. Local authorities must take account of a family’s needs when planning care for a child in so far as is consistent with the welfare of a child (which remains paramount), as set out in guidance on care placements, available at: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/children-act-1989-care-planning-placement-and-case-review. Where it is not possible, or appropriate, to place siblings together, siblings must be supported to understand the reasons why. Contact arrangements between siblings must be robust and remain under independent review.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","63208 ; 63302","2017-02-09T13:16:55.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685477/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685477/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685477/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-06","Children in Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many looked-after children who have one or more siblings have (a) been placed and (b) not been placed with their siblings in each of the last three years; and of those children who were not placed with their siblings (i) how many have contact with the siblings they are separated from and (ii) what the frequency is of that contact.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","63207"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685478","Department for Education","false","2017-02-13","<p>We are committed to ensuring that all children receive a high quality education, regardless of where they attend school. We are, therefore, spending £70 million over this Parliament to reduce the attainment gap, in line with the recommendations in Sir Nick Weller’s report.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-02-13T11:17:16.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685478/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685478/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685478/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-06","GCSE","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps she is taking to reduce the attainment gaps of five A* to C GCSE grades between secondary schools in the North and the South; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","63212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685479","Department for Education","false","2017-02-14","<p>The Department has not received any representations on the effect of university and college diversity officers on academic freedom.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-02-14T16:49:13.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685479/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685479/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685479/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-06","Academic Freedom","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what representation she has received on the effect of university and college diversity officers on academic freedom.","false","Biography information for Michael Gove","Surrey Heath","Michael Gove","63173"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685480","Department for Education","false","2017-02-10","<p>The Department’s financial system has never held information centrally that distinguished suppliers belonging to the voluntary and charitable sector. A manual process to identify them was discontinued in May 2014, when it was no longer required by the Cabinet Office.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-02-10T14:04:11.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685480/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685480/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/685480/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-06","Department for Education: Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 7 December 2016 to Question 56626, for what reasons information that was held centrally from 2010 to 2014 on which charitable organisations her Department funds is no longer held centrally.","false","Biography information for Michael Gove","Surrey Heath","Michael Gove","63174"
